			<div class="current-exhibit-wrapper">
				<h2 class="body-current-exhibit">Current Exhibit:</h2>

				<p class="body-artists">Join us on Saturday October 3 from 6-9PM at the Poverty &amp; the Arts Studio &amp; Gallery for the latest show by our PovA artists, "Exploring Autumn". The show will feature 7 artists that have or are experiencing homelessness in our Artist Collective. Working with acrylic paints, pastels, mixed media, and reuse material, our artists have created an exciting and unique show to explore the various ways fall means something to them. This is a show you're not going to want to miss!</p>

			</div>

			<h2 class="body-current-exhibit">About the gallery:</h2>

			<p class="body-copy light grey">Poverty &amp; the Arts is a Nashville-based nonprofit that supports homeless and formerly homeless individuals by providing an environment that fosters creativity and strengthens community relationships. Through the offered arts programming, the Poverty &amp; the Arts artists are able to develop confidence and determination, income-generating opportunities, job skills, and community relationships. Volunteers interact directly with homeless participants in an effort to break down stereotypes and encourage relationships that are critical in breaking the cycle of homelessness. The artists in the PovA Artist Collective are pursuing art and creativity as a means to make real, sustainable change in their lives. In addition to earning 60% of the sale of any original piece of art, the artists gain valuable artistic and business skills through the program. Art is a way for our artists to find beauty in the midst of their daily struggles, and it inspires them to move forward. Art also facilitates a space for our community members to view our homeless as a creative and talented part of that community.</p>

